### Bug Bounty Practice — OWASP crAPI

Skills developed through structured bug bounty practice against OWASP crAPI,
a deliberately vulnerable API application aligned with the OWASP API Security Top 10.

#### Vulnerability Types Identified
- Insecure Direct Object Reference (IDOR)
- Broken Object Level Authorization (BOLA)
- JWT Algorithm None Attack
- Information Disclosure Leading to Authorization Bypass

#### Techniques Practiced
- Sequential ID Enumeration & Manipulation
- Parameter Tampering (URL & JSON Body)
- JWT Token Manipulation
- Vulnerability Chaining (Data Leak → IDOR)
- API Endpoint Discovery & Analysis
- Burp Suite (Intercept, Modify, Replay)
